			IF ELSE STATEMENT:

It is a extension of simple if statement.
If test expression is true,then the true block statement, immediately following 
the if statement are executed;otherwise the false block statement() are executed.
In either case, either true-block(or) false block will be executed, not both.


syntax:

if(test expression)
{
	True block  statement;
}
else
{
	false block statement;
}
statement -x;


Example:
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
	int a=5;
	if(a<10)
	{
		printf("%d is less than 10\n",a);
	}
	else
	{
		printf("%d is greater than 10\n",a);
	}
	return 0;
}


output:
5 is less than 10

